Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt and @pepper. Sprinkle with the @lemon & herb seasoning{1%sachet}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pop the @British hickory smoked sausages{2} onto a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> Alternatively, cook them on the BBQ if you'd prefer.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages. They're cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{150%grams} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Once hot, fry the sweetcorn until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the corn to pick up some nice colour. Transfer to a large #bowl{}.

While the corn chars, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt and @pepper and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%grams}. Zest and halve the @lime{1}.

When the onions are golden, add the @sugar for the onions{1%tsp} to the saucepan and cook until caramelised, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Pop the @British chicken thighs{3} into a medium bowl with the @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet} and a drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @salt and @pepper, then turn to coat the chicken in the spice.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in the (now empty) corn frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the spiced chicken thighs flat in the pan. Fry until browned on each side and cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins.

> Alternatively, cook on the BBQ if you'd prefer.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Lime Dressing ==

Squeeze the lime juice into a small bowl. Add the @sugar for the dressing{1%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt and @pepper, then mix well.

Add the @coleslaw mix{120%grams} to the bowl of charred corn. Pour in the lime dressing and toss to coat.

== Assembly ==

When the chicken is cooked, remove from the heat. Drizzle with the @honey{15%grams}, turning the chicken to glaze it.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Slice the @brioche hot dog buns{2} top down through the middle (but not all the way through) and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the wedges are cooked, sprinkle over the lime zest. Toss to coat.

Spread the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} inside the buns and spoon in the caramelised onions. Top with the sausages and sprinkle with the grated cheese.

Serve your peri peri chicken with the loaded sausages in buns, corn slaw and wedges on the side. Enjoy!